{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H5EhnmaH7Hm1GxZ5Ef8rkZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { Hono } from \"hono\";\n     2→import { cors } from \"hono/cors\";\n     3→import { serve } from \"@hono/node-server\";\n     4→import { Connection, PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n     5→import postgres from \"postgres\";\n     6→import { loadConfig } from \"./config.js\";\n     7→import { createDb } from \"./db.js\";\n     8→import { createAuthDb } from \"./auth-db.js\";\n     9→import { createCoinflipRoutes } from \"./routes/create.js\";\n    10→import { createLordRoutes } from \"./routes/lord-create.js\";\n    11→import { createRoundsRoutes } from \"./routes/rounds.js\";\n    12→import { createCloseCallRoutes } from \"./routes/closecall.js\";\n    13→import { createHealthRoutes } from \"./routes/health.js\";\n    14→import { createAuthRoutes } from \"./routes/auth.js\";\n    15→import { createJwtAuthMiddleware } from \"./middleware/jwt-auth.js\";\n    16→import { createRateLimitMiddleware } from \"./middleware/rate-limit.js\";\n    17→import { createSettlementWorker } from \"./worker/settlement.js\";\n    18→import { settleRound } from \"./worker/settle-tx.js\";\n    19→import { createRetrySettler } from \"./worker/retry.js\";\n    20→import { createPdaWatcher } from \"./worker/pda-watcher.js\";\n    21→import { createCloseCallClockWorker } from \"./worker/closecall-clock.js\";\n    22→import { logger } from \"./logger.js\";\n    23→\n    24→const config = loadConfig();\n    25→\n    26→// Shared postgres connection for both game DB and auth DB\n    27→const sql = postgres(config.databaseUrl);\n    28→const db = createDb(config.databaseUrl);\n    29→const authDb = createAuthDb(sql);\n    30→\n    31→const connection = new Connection(config.rpcUrl, {\n    32→  commitment: \"confirmed\",\n    33→  ...(config.wsRpcUrl ? { wsEndpoint: config.wsRpcUrl } : {}),\n    34→});\n    35→\n    36→const app = new Hono();\n    37→\n    38→app.use(\n    39→  \"*\",\n    40→  cors({\n    41→    origin: \"*\",\n    42→    allowMethods: [\"GET\", \"POST\", \"OPTIONS\"],\n    43→    allowHeaders: [\"Content-Type\", \"Authorization\"],\n    44→  }),\n    45→);\n    46→\n    47→// Request logging — correlate frontend fetch timing with server-side processing\n    48→app.use(\"*\", async (c, next) => {\n    49→  const start = Date.now();\n    50→  await next();\n    51→  const ms = Date.now() - start;\n    52→  const method = c.req.method;\n    53→  const path = c.req.path;\n    54→  // Skip noisy health checks and OPTIONS preflight\n    55→  if (path === \"/health\" || method === \"OPTIONS\") return;\n    56→  logger.debug(\"request\", { method, path, status: c.res.status, ms });\n    57→});\n    58→\n    59→// Auth routes — no JWT middleware (these are the login endpoints)\n    60→// Lighter rate limiting by IP for auth endpoints\n    61→app.use(\n    62→  \"/auth/*\",\n    63→  createRateLimitMiddleware({\n    64→    perWallet: 20,\n    65→    global: config.rateLimitGlobal,\n    66→    windowMs: 60_000,\n    67→  }),\n    68→);\n    69→\n    70→app.route(\n    71→  \"/auth\",\n    72→  createAuthRoutes({\n    73→    authDb,\n    74→    jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret,\n    75→    cluster: config.cluster,\n    76→    challengeTtlSeconds: config.challengeTtlSeconds,\n    77→    accessTokenTtlSeconds: config.accessTokenTtlSeconds,\n    78→    refreshTokenTtlDays: config.refreshTokenTtlDays,\n    79→  }),\n    80→);\n    81→\n    82→// JWT auth middleware for fairness endpoints\n    83→app.use(\n    84→  \"/fairness/*\",\n    85→  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret }),\n    86→);\n    87→\n    88→// Rate limiting — per-wallet and global limits on POST requests\n    89→app.use(\n    90→  \"/fairness/*\",\n    91→  createRateLimitMiddleware({\n    92→    perWallet: config.rateLimitPerWallet,\n    93→    global: config.rateLimitGlobal,\n    94→    windowMs: 60_000,\n    95→  }),\n    96→);\n    97→\n    98→// Settlement infrastructure — must be created before routes (routes use pdaWatcher)\n    99→const entropyAccount = new PublicKey(config.entropyAccount);\n   100→const retrySettler = createRetrySettler({"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VjBSw9tMWntCUQGUX3iNN9","session_id":"402c21eb-b534-4fb0-8000-5dcbddbea423","uuid":"558200ba-47a0-493d-8bde-7502d4124359"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a62e3bc930d39da7c","tool_use_id":"toolu_01VjBSw9tMWntCUQGUX3iNN9","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore price-feeds and API patterns","usage":{"total_tokens":72762,"tool_uses":43,"duration_ms":179086},"uuid":"2c9f9fcc-31cd-46ce-bff6-3b5a16994bdc","session_id":"402c21eb-b534-4fb0-8000-5dcbddbea423"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VjBSw9tMWntCUQGUX3iNN9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Code Analysis Report\n\n### 1. Price Feeds Package (`sources/rng-utopia/packages/price-feeds/`)\n\n#### Export List (`src/index.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport { PriceFeedProvider, usePriceSubscription } from \"./PriceFeedProvider\";\nexport { SUPPORTED_ASSETS, type Asset, type PriceData, type Candle } from \"./types\";\n```\n\n#### Full `PriceFeedProvider.tsx` Implementation:\n\n**Hook Usage Pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport function usePriceSubscription(asset: Asset): PriceData | null\n```\n\nThe hook:\n- Auto-subscribes to a price asset on mount via `useEffect`\n- Returns the latest `PriceData` for that asset or `null` if not yet received\n- Auto-unsubscribes on unmount\n- Throws error if used outside `PriceFeedProvider`\n\n**Provider Implementation:**\n- Creates a **WebSocket connection to Pyth** (`https://hermes.pyth.network/ws` by default, configurable)\n- Sends subscription message: `{ type: \"subscribe\", ids: [feed_id1, feed_id2, ...] }`\n- On `price_update` message, decodes and stores price data in React state\n- Supports multiple concurrent subscriptions\n- The provider manages a `Map<Asset, PriceData>` internally\n\n**Data Types (`types.ts`):**\n```typescript\nexport type Asset = \"BTC\" | \"ETH\" | \"SOL\";\n\nexport interface PriceData {\n  asset: Asset;\n  price: number;\n  confidence: number;\n  timestamp: number;\n  publishTime: number;\n}\n\nexport const PYTH_FEED_IDS: Record<Asset, string> = {\n  BTC: \"0xe62df6c8b4a85fe1a67db44dc12de5db330f7ac66b72dc658afedf0f4a415b43\",\n  ETH: \"0xff61491a931112ddf1bd8147cd1b641375f79f5825126d665480874634fd0ace\",\n  SOL: \"0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d\",\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Coinflip Context Pattern (`apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx`)\n\n#### Architecture Pattern - Three-Level Data Fetch:\n\n**1. Backend URL Configuration:**\n```typescript\nconst FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL = (\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n```\n- Reads from `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` env var\n- Falls back to localhost:3100 for dev\n- Strips trailing slash\n\n**.env Files:**\n- **`.env.example`**: Generic Solana config (RPC URL, network, no backend URL)\n- **`.env.devnet`**: \n  ```\n  VITE_RPC_URL=https://lb.drpc.live/solana-devnet/...\n  VITE_WS_RPC_URL=wss://lb.drpc.live/solana-devnet/...\n  VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3100\n  VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\n  VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\n  VITE_LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID=B9Lufh9GvuucDxDRZBr3qPNe4cJaS5MQBQKZxgUT5qYa\n  ```\n\n**2. Backend API Calls in Coinflip:**\n\n**Match Creation:**\n```typescript\nexport async function buildBackendCreateMatchTx(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  amountSol: number,\n  side: CoinSide,\n  accessToken: string,\n): Promise<{ transaction: Transaction; matchPda: PublicKey; commitment: string }> {\n  const payload = {\n    wallet: creator.toBase58(),\n    amountLamports: Math.round(amountSol * 1e9),\n    side: COIN_SIDE_VALUES[side],\n  };\n\n  const response = await fetch(getFairnessBackendCreateUrl(), {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: {\n      \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n      \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${accessToken}`,\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify(payload),\n  });\n\n  const json = await parseBackendResponse<BackendCreateMatchResponse>(response);\n\n  return {\n    transaction: Transaction.from(Buffer.from(json.transaction, \"base64\")),\n    matchPda: new PublicKey(json.matchPda),\n    commitment: json.commitment,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Request Response Types:**\n```typescript\nexport interface BackendCreateMatchResponse {\n  transaction: string;        // base64-encoded Transaction\n  matchPda: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  commitment: string;\n  lastValidBlockHeight: number;\n}\n\nexport interface BackendRoundResponse {\n  pda: string;\n  game: string;\n  phase: \"created\" | \"locked\" | \"settling\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\";\n  creator: string;\n  commitment: string;\n  amountLamports: number;\n  side: number;\n  matchId: string;\n  createdAt: string;\n  updatedAt: string;\n  targetSlot?: number;\n  secret?: string;\n  resultHash?: string | null;\n  resultSide?: number | null;\n  winner?: string | null;\n  settleTx?: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Round Verification (Settlement Detection):**\n```typescript\nexport async function fetchRoundVerification(\n  matchPda: string\n): Promise<BackendRoundResponse | null> {\n  const response = await fetch(getFairnessBackendRoundUrl(matchPda));\n  if (response.status === 404) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return parseBackendResponse<BackendRoundResponse>(response);\n}\n\nfunction getFairnessBackendRoundUrl(matchPda: string): string {\n  return `${FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL}/fairness/rounds/${matchPda}`;\n}\n\nfunction getFairnessBackendCreateUrl(): string {\n  return `${FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL}/fairness/coinflip/create`;\n}\n```\n\n**Deep-Link Round Fetch by Match ID:**\n```typescript\nexport async function fetchMatchByMatchId(\n  connection: Connection,\n  matchId: string,\n): Promise<UIMatch | null> {\n  const response = await fetch(`${FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL}/fairness/rounds/by-id/${matchId}`);\n  if (!response.ok) return null;\n  const backendRound = (await response.json()) as BackendRoundResponse;\n  // ... merge on-chain + backend data\n}\n```\n\n**3. Polling & Event Detection:**\n\nThe context uses a **two-pronged approach** for settlement:\n\n1. **WebSocket PDA Monitoring** (`useSettlementEvent` hook):\n   - Watches the match account via `onAccountChange`\n   - Fires immediately when PDA closes (lamports→0) after server settlement\n   - Fallback to polling every 3-5 seconds\n\n2. **Polling Fallback:**\n   ```typescript\n   const pollInterval = activeMatch\n     ? (activeMatch.phase === \"countdown\" || activeMatch.phase === \"flipping\" \n        ? 2000    // 2s during animation\n        : 5000)   // 5s otherwise\n     : 30000;    // 30s in lobby\n   ```\n\n3. **Phase Transition Logic:**\n   - When opponent joins: `created → ready` → starts countdown/flip animation\n   - During animation: holds result in state, waits for flip timer to show it\n   - After settlement: `ready → complete` or `complete` detected via poll\n   - PDA disappears after settlement → fetches backend round for final proof\n\n---\n\n### 3. Backend API for Close Call (`services/backend/src/routes/closecall.ts`)\n\n**Full Route Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface CloseCallRoutesDeps {\n  db: Db;\n}\n\nfunction formatCloseCallRound(round: CloseCallRound) {\n  const totalPool = round.green_pool + round.red_pool;\n  return {\n    roundId: round.round_id,\n    pda: round.pda,\n    phase: round.phase,\n    openPrice: round.open_price,\n    openPriceExpo: round.open_price_expo,\n    closePrice: round.close_price,\n    outcome: round.outcome,\n    greenPool: round.green_pool,\n    redPool: round.red_pool,\n    totalPool,\n    totalFee: round.total_fee,\n    greenEntries: round.green_entries,\n    redEntries: round.red_entries,\n    greenCount: round.green_entries.length,\n    redCount: round.red_entries.length,\n    settleTx: round.settle_tx,\n    createdAt: round.created_at.toISOString(),\n    settledAt: round.settled_at ? round.settled_at.toISOString() : null,\n  };\n}\n\nexport function createCloseCallRoutes(deps: CloseCallRoutesDeps): Hono {\n  const { db } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono();\n\n  // GET /closecall/current-round\n  app.get(\"/current-round\", async (c) => {\n    const round = await db.getCloseCallCurrentRound();\n    if (!round) {\n      return c.json({ round: null });\n    }\n    return c.json({ round: formatCloseCallRound(round) });\n  });\n\n  // GET /closecall/history?limit=20 (max 100)\n  app.get(\"/history\", async (c) => {\n    const limitParam = c.req.query(\"limit\");\n    const limit = Math.min(Math.max(parseInt(limitParam ?? \"20\", 10) || 20, 1), 100);\n    const rounds = await db.getCloseCallHistory(limit);\n    return c.json({ rounds: rounds.map(formatCloseCallRound) });\n  });\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Database Types (`db.ts`):**\n```typescript\nexport type CloseCallPhase = \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\";\nexport type CloseCallOutcome = \"pending\" | \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\";\n\nexport interface CloseCallRound {\n  round_id: string;\n  pda: string;\n  server_key: string;\n  phase: CloseCallPhase;\n  open_price: number;\n  open_price_expo: number;\n  close_price: number | null;\n  outcome: CloseCallOutcome;\n  green_pool: number;\n  red_pool: number;\n  total_fee: number;\n  green_entries: Array<{ player: string; amountLamports: number }>;\n  red_entries: Array<{ player: string; amountLamports: number }>;\n  settle_tx: string | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n  settled_at: Date | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Response Shapes:**\n\n`GET /closecall/current-round`:\n```json\n{\n  \"round\": {\n    \"roundId\": \"a1b2c3d4e5f6g7h8\",\n    \"pda\": \"FarmABC...\",\n    \"phase\": \"open\",\n    \"openPrice\": 45000.50,\n    \"openPriceExpo\": -2,\n    \"closePrice\": null,\n    \"outcome\": \"pending\",\n    \"greenPool\": 5.25,\n    \"redPool\": 3.75,\n    \"totalPool\": 9.0,\n    \"totalFee\": 0.27,\n    \"greenEntries\": [\n      { \"player\": \"wallet1...\", \"amountLamports\": 1000000000 },\n      { \"player\": \"wallet2...\", \"amountLamports\": 4250000000 }\n    ],\n    \"redEntries\": [\n      { \"player\": \"wallet3...\", \"amountLamports\": 3750000000 }\n    ],\n    \"greenCount\": 2,\n    \"redCount\": 1,\n    \"settleTx\": null,\n    \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-18T12:30:00.000Z\",\n    \"settledAt\": null\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`GET /closecall/history?limit=5`:\n```json\n{\n  \"rounds\": [\n    { /* formatCloseCallRound output */ },\n    { /* ... */ }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Config/Env Patterns\n\n**Auth API Configuration** (`apps/platform/src/lib/auth-api.ts`):\n```typescript\nconst BACKEND_URL = (\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n\n// Example usage:\nexport async function requestChallenge(wallet: string): Promise<ChallengeResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/challenge`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ wallet }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<ChallengeResponse>(res);\n}\n\nexport async function verifyChallenge(\n  nonce: string,\n  wallet: string,\n  signature: string,\n): Promise<VerifyResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/verify`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ nonce, wallet, signature }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<VerifyResponse>(res);\n}\n\nexport async function refreshSession(refreshToken: string): Promise<RefreshResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/refresh`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<RefreshResponse>(res);\n}\n```\n\n**Backend Server Setup** (`services/backend/src/index.ts`):\n```typescript\nconst app = new Hono();\n\napp.use(\"*\", cors({\n  origin: \"*\",\n  allowMethods: [\"GET\", \"POST\", \"OPTIONS\"],\n  allowHeaders: [\"Content-Type\", \"Authorization\"],\n}));\n\n// Auth routes (no JWT middleware)\napp.route(\"/auth\", createAuthRoutes({\n  authDb,\n  jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret,\n  cluster: config.cluster,\n  challengeTtlSeconds: config.challengeTtlSeconds,\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds: config.accessTokenTtlSeconds,\n  refreshTokenTtlDays: config.refreshTokenTtlDays,\n}));\n\n// Fairness routes (with JWT middleware)\napp.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret }));\n\n// Game routes\napp.route(\"/fairness\", createCoinflipRoutes({ /* ... */ }));\napp.route(\"/fairness\", createLordRoutes({ /* ... */ }));\napp.route(\"/closecall\", createCloseCallRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Close Call Context (Frontend Mock) (`apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx`)\n\n**Context Pattern:**\n- Currently uses **mock simulation** (no real backend integration yet)\n- Manages round state, user bets, pool tracking, candle history\n- Real backend will be injected when Close Call ships\n\n**Key Differences from Coinflip:**\n- **Centralized polling** (100ms for price interpolation)\n- **No WebSocket PDA watching** (uses mock event emitter)\n- **Pari-mutuel pool calculation** (shared winner pool, not 1v1)\n- **Price feed integration** (depends on Pyth BTC/ETH/SOL prices)\n\n**Context Value:**\n```typescript\ninterface CloseCallContextValue {\n  currentRound: Round | null;\n  completedRound: Round | null;\n  recentCandles: Candle[];\n  currentPrice: number;\n  candleProgress: number;           // 0.0 to 1.0 during candle\n  userHistory: UserRoundHistory[];\n\n  pendingAmount: number;\n  pendingSide: BetSide | null;      // \"green\" | \"red\"\n  userBet: PlayerBet | null;        // from currentRound.pool\n\n  loading: boolean;\n  placingBet: boolean;\n\n  setPendingAmount: (amount: number) => void;\n  setPendingSide: (side: BetSide | null) => void;\n  placeBet: (side?: BetSide) => Promise<void>;\n  adjustBetAmount: (adj: \"half\" | \"double\" | \"max\") => void;\n  clearCompletedRound: () => void;\n\n  potentialPayout: number;\n  userOdds: number;\n  refreshRound: () => void;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\n1. **Backend URL Pattern**: \n   - Single env var: `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` (points to backend root, e.g., `http://localhost:3100`)\n   - All routes use suffix: `/fairness/*` (coinflip, lord), `/closecall/*`, `/auth/*`\n   - Default fallback: `http://127.0.0.1:3100`\n\n2. **Polling & Event Detection**:\n   - Coinflip: WebSocket PDA monitoring + fallback polling (2-5s during active play)\n   - Close Call: Polling only (100ms for price, 5-30s for rounds)\n\n3. **Authorization**:\n   - Auth endpoints: No JWT required (`/auth/*`)\n   - Fairness endpoints: JWT Bearer token in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n\n4. **Price Feeds**:\n   - Pyth live WebSocket (configurable endpoint)\n   - Assets: BTC, ETH, SOL\n   - Direct consumption via `usePriceSubscription(asset)` hook\n\n5. **Data Flow**:\n   - Backend builds transactions, frontend signs and confirms on-chain\n   - Backend polls/watches on-chain events and settles via coordinator\n   - Frontend polls backend for settlement proof after on-chain event detected\n\nAll file paths are absolute and ready for reference."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a62e3bc930d39da7c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 77338\ntool_uses: 43\nduration_ms: 179112</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"402c21eb-b534-4fb0-8000-5dcbddbea423","uuid":"3558af9a-3e5e-4f69-b384-d7e12013dfe2","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughness: very thorough\n\nI need to understand:\n\n1. **Price feeds package**: Read `sources/rng-utopia/packages/price-feeds/src/index.ts` (or wherever the barrel export is). Find the `usePriceSubscription` hook or equivalent that provides live BTC price data. Show me the full export list and how the hook is used.\n\n2. **Coinflip context pattern**: Read `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` (or similar). I need to see the pattern for:\n   - How it fetches data from the backend API\n   - How polling is implemented\n   - What the API base URL pattern is (e.g., `useBackendUrl()` or `BACKEND_URL` config)\n\n3. **Backend API for closecall**: Read `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/closecall.ts` to understand the exact response shapes of `GET /closecall/current-round` and `GET /closecall/history`.\n\n4. **Config/env pattern**: How does the frontend know the backend URL? Check `sources/rng-utopia/packages/config/` or `apps/platform/src/` for `BACKEND_URL` or `API_URL` config patterns.\n\nReturn ALL the content for each file, not summaries.","agentId":"a62e3bc930d39da7c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Code Analysis Report\n\n### 1. Price Feeds Package (`sources/rng-utopia/packages/price-feeds/`)\n\n#### Export List (`src/index.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport { PriceFeedProvider, usePriceSubscription } from \"./PriceFeedProvider\";\nexport { SUPPORTED_ASSETS, type Asset, type PriceData, type Candle } from \"./types\";\n```\n\n#### Full `PriceFeedProvider.tsx` Implementation:\n\n**Hook Usage Pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport function usePriceSubscription(asset: Asset): PriceData | null\n```\n\nThe hook:\n- Auto-subscribes to a price asset on mount via `useEffect`\n- Returns the latest `PriceData` for that asset or `null` if not yet received\n- Auto-unsubscribes on unmount\n- Throws error if used outside `PriceFeedProvider`\n\n**Provider Implementation:**\n- Creates a **WebSocket connection to Pyth** (`https://hermes.pyth.network/ws` by default, configurable)\n- Sends subscription message: `{ type: \"subscribe\", ids: [feed_id1, feed_id2, ...] }`\n- On `price_update` message, decodes and stores price data in React state\n- Supports multiple concurrent subscriptions\n- The provider manages a `Map<Asset, PriceData>` internally\n\n**Data Types (`types.ts`):**\n```typescript\nexport type Asset = \"BTC\" | \"ETH\" | \"SOL\";\n\nexport interface PriceData {\n  asset: Asset;\n  price: number;\n  confidence: number;\n  timestamp: number;\n  publishTime: number;\n}\n\nexport const PYTH_FEED_IDS: Record<Asset, string> = {\n  BTC: \"0xe62df6c8b4a85fe1a67db44dc12de5db330f7ac66b72dc658afedf0f4a415b43\",\n  ETH: \"0xff61491a931112ddf1bd8147cd1b641375f79f5825126d665480874634fd0ace\",\n  SOL: \"0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d\",\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Coinflip Context Pattern (`apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx`)\n\n#### Architecture Pattern - Three-Level Data Fetch:\n\n**1. Backend URL Configuration:**\n```typescript\nconst FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL = (\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n```\n- Reads from `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` env var\n- Falls back to localhost:3100 for dev\n- Strips trailing slash\n\n**.env Files:**\n- **`.env.example`**: Generic Solana config (RPC URL, network, no backend URL)\n- **`.env.devnet`**: \n  ```\n  VITE_RPC_URL=https://lb.drpc.live/solana-devnet/...\n  VITE_WS_RPC_URL=wss://lb.drpc.live/solana-devnet/...\n  VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3100\n  VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\n  VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\n  VITE_LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID=B9Lufh9GvuucDxDRZBr3qPNe4cJaS5MQBQKZxgUT5qYa\n  ```\n\n**2. Backend API Calls in Coinflip:**\n\n**Match Creation:**\n```typescript\nexport async function buildBackendCreateMatchTx(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  amountSol: number,\n  side: CoinSide,\n  accessToken: string,\n): Promise<{ transaction: Transaction; matchPda: PublicKey; commitment: string }> {\n  const payload = {\n    wallet: creator.toBase58(),\n    amountLamports: Math.round(amountSol * 1e9),\n    side: COIN_SIDE_VALUES[side],\n  };\n\n  const response = await fetch(getFairnessBackendCreateUrl(), {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: {\n      \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n      \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${accessToken}`,\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify(payload),\n  });\n\n  const json = await parseBackendResponse<BackendCreateMatchResponse>(response);\n\n  return {\n    transaction: Transaction.from(Buffer.from(json.transaction, \"base64\")),\n    matchPda: new PublicKey(json.matchPda),\n    commitment: json.commitment,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Request Response Types:**\n```typescript\nexport interface BackendCreateMatchResponse {\n  transaction: string;        // base64-encoded Transaction\n  matchPda: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  commitment: string;\n  lastValidBlockHeight: number;\n}\n\nexport interface BackendRoundResponse {\n  pda: string;\n  game: string;\n  phase: \"created\" | \"locked\" | \"settling\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\";\n  creator: string;\n  commitment: string;\n  amountLamports: number;\n  side: number;\n  matchId: string;\n  createdAt: string;\n  updatedAt: string;\n  targetSlot?: number;\n  secret?: string;\n  resultHash?: string | null;\n  resultSide?: number | null;\n  winner?: string | null;\n  settleTx?: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Round Verification (Settlement Detection):**\n```typescript\nexport async function fetchRoundVerification(\n  matchPda: string\n): Promise<BackendRoundResponse | null> {\n  const response = await fetch(getFairnessBackendRoundUrl(matchPda));\n  if (response.status === 404) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return parseBackendResponse<BackendRoundResponse>(response);\n}\n\nfunction getFairnessBackendRoundUrl(matchPda: string): string {\n  return `${FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL}/fairness/rounds/${matchPda}`;\n}\n\nfunction getFairnessBackendCreateUrl(): string {\n  return `${FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL}/fairness/coinflip/create`;\n}\n```\n\n**Deep-Link Round Fetch by Match ID:**\n```typescript\nexport async function fetchMatchByMatchId(\n  connection: Connection,\n  matchId: string,\n): Promise<UIMatch | null> {\n  const response = await fetch(`${FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL}/fairness/rounds/by-id/${matchId}`);\n  if (!response.ok) return null;\n  const backendRound = (await response.json()) as BackendRoundResponse;\n  // ... merge on-chain + backend data\n}\n```\n\n**3. Polling & Event Detection:**\n\nThe context uses a **two-pronged approach** for settlement:\n\n1. **WebSocket PDA Monitoring** (`useSettlementEvent` hook):\n   - Watches the match account via `onAccountChange`\n   - Fires immediately when PDA closes (lamports→0) after server settlement\n   - Fallback to polling every 3-5 seconds\n\n2. **Polling Fallback:**\n   ```typescript\n   const pollInterval = activeMatch\n     ? (activeMatch.phase === \"countdown\" || activeMatch.phase === \"flipping\" \n        ? 2000    // 2s during animation\n        : 5000)   // 5s otherwise\n     : 30000;    // 30s in lobby\n   ```\n\n3. **Phase Transition Logic:**\n   - When opponent joins: `created → ready` → starts countdown/flip animation\n   - During animation: holds result in state, waits for flip timer to show it\n   - After settlement: `ready → complete` or `complete` detected via poll\n   - PDA disappears after settlement → fetches backend round for final proof\n\n---\n\n### 3. Backend API for Close Call (`services/backend/src/routes/closecall.ts`)\n\n**Full Route Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface CloseCallRoutesDeps {\n  db: Db;\n}\n\nfunction formatCloseCallRound(round: CloseCallRound) {\n  const totalPool = round.green_pool + round.red_pool;\n  return {\n    roundId: round.round_id,\n    pda: round.pda,\n    phase: round.phase,\n    openPrice: round.open_price,\n    openPriceExpo: round.open_price_expo,\n    closePrice: round.close_price,\n    outcome: round.outcome,\n    greenPool: round.green_pool,\n    redPool: round.red_pool,\n    totalPool,\n    totalFee: round.total_fee,\n    greenEntries: round.green_entries,\n    redEntries: round.red_entries,\n    greenCount: round.green_entries.length,\n    redCount: round.red_entries.length,\n    settleTx: round.settle_tx,\n    createdAt: round.created_at.toISOString(),\n    settledAt: round.settled_at ? round.settled_at.toISOString() : null,\n  };\n}\n\nexport function createCloseCallRoutes(deps: CloseCallRoutesDeps): Hono {\n  const { db } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono();\n\n  // GET /closecall/current-round\n  app.get(\"/current-round\", async (c) => {\n    const round = await db.getCloseCallCurrentRound();\n    if (!round) {\n      return c.json({ round: null });\n    }\n    return c.json({ round: formatCloseCallRound(round) });\n  });\n\n  // GET /closecall/history?limit=20 (max 100)\n  app.get(\"/history\", async (c) => {\n    const limitParam = c.req.query(\"limit\");\n    const limit = Math.min(Math.max(parseInt(limitParam ?? \"20\", 10) || 20, 1), 100);\n    const rounds = await db.getCloseCallHistory(limit);\n    return c.json({ rounds: rounds.map(formatCloseCallRound) });\n  });\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Database Types (`db.ts`):**\n```typescript\nexport type CloseCallPhase = \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\";\nexport type CloseCallOutcome = \"pending\" | \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\";\n\nexport interface CloseCallRound {\n  round_id: string;\n  pda: string;\n  server_key: string;\n  phase: CloseCallPhase;\n  open_price: number;\n  open_price_expo: number;\n  close_price: number | null;\n  outcome: CloseCallOutcome;\n  green_pool: number;\n  red_pool: number;\n  total_fee: number;\n  green_entries: Array<{ player: string; amountLamports: number }>;\n  red_entries: Array<{ player: string; amountLamports: number }>;\n  settle_tx: string | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n  settled_at: Date | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Response Shapes:**\n\n`GET /closecall/current-round`:\n```json\n{\n  \"round\": {\n    \"roundId\": \"a1b2c3d4e5f6g7h8\",\n    \"pda\": \"FarmABC...\",\n    \"phase\": \"open\",\n    \"openPrice\": 45000.50,\n    \"openPriceExpo\": -2,\n    \"closePrice\": null,\n    \"outcome\": \"pending\",\n    \"greenPool\": 5.25,\n    \"redPool\": 3.75,\n    \"totalPool\": 9.0,\n    \"totalFee\": 0.27,\n    \"greenEntries\": [\n      { \"player\": \"wallet1...\", \"amountLamports\": 1000000000 },\n      { \"player\": \"wallet2...\", \"amountLamports\": 4250000000 }\n    ],\n    \"redEntries\": [\n      { \"player\": \"wallet3...\", \"amountLamports\": 3750000000 }\n    ],\n    \"greenCount\": 2,\n    \"redCount\": 1,\n    \"settleTx\": null,\n    \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-18T12:30:00.000Z\",\n    \"settledAt\": null\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`GET /closecall/history?limit=5`:\n```json\n{\n  \"rounds\": [\n    { /* formatCloseCallRound output */ },\n    { /* ... */ }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Config/Env Patterns\n\n**Auth API Configuration** (`apps/platform/src/lib/auth-api.ts`):\n```typescript\nconst BACKEND_URL = (\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n\n// Example usage:\nexport async function requestChallenge(wallet: string): Promise<ChallengeResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/challenge`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ wallet }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<ChallengeResponse>(res);\n}\n\nexport async function verifyChallenge(\n  nonce: string,\n  wallet: string,\n  signature: string,\n): Promise<VerifyResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/verify`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ nonce, wallet, signature }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<VerifyResponse>(res);\n}\n\nexport async function refreshSession(refreshToken: string): Promise<RefreshResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/refresh`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<RefreshResponse>(res);\n}\n```\n\n**Backend Server Setup** (`services/backend/src/index.ts`):\n```typescript\nconst app = new Hono();\n\napp.use(\"*\", cors({\n  origin: \"*\",\n  allowMethods: [\"GET\", \"POST\", \"OPTIONS\"],\n  allowHeaders: [\"Content-Type\", \"Authorization\"],\n}));\n\n// Auth routes (no JWT middleware)\napp.route(\"/auth\", createAuthRoutes({\n  authDb,\n  jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret,\n  cluster: config.cluster,\n  challengeTtlSeconds: config.challengeTtlSeconds,\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds: config.accessTokenTtlSeconds,\n  refreshTokenTtlDays: config.refreshTokenTtlDays,\n}));\n\n// Fairness routes (with JWT middleware)\napp.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret }));\n\n// Game routes\napp.route(\"/fairness\", createCoinflipRoutes({ /* ... */ }));\napp.route(\"/fairness\", createLordRoutes({ /* ... */ }));\napp.route(\"/closecall\", createCloseCallRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Close Call Context (Frontend Mock) (`apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx`)\n\n**Context Pattern:**\n- Currently uses **mock simulation** (no real backend integration yet)\n- Manages round state, user bets, pool tracking, candle history\n- Real backend will be injected when Close Call ships\n\n**Key Differences from Coinflip:**\n- **Centralized polling** (100ms for price interpolation)\n- **No WebSocket PDA watching** (uses mock event emitter)\n- **Pari-mutuel pool calculation** (shared winner pool, not 1v1)\n- **Price feed integration** (depends on Pyth BTC/ETH/SOL prices)\n\n**Context Value:**\n```typescript\ninterface CloseCallContextValue {\n  currentRound: Round | null;\n  completedRound: Round | null;\n  recentCandles: Candle[];\n  currentPrice: number;\n  candleProgress: number;           // 0.0 to 1.0 during candle\n  userHistory: UserRoundHistory[];\n\n  pendingAmount: number;\n  pendingSide: BetSide | null;      // \"green\" | \"red\"\n  userBet: PlayerBet | null;        // from currentRound.pool\n\n  loading: boolean;\n  placingBet: boolean;\n\n  setPendingAmount: (amount: number) => void;\n  setPendingSide: (side: BetSide | null) => void;\n  placeBet: (side?: BetSide) => Promise<void>;\n  adjustBetAmount: (adj: \"half\" | \"double\" | \"max\") => void;\n  clearCompletedRound: () => void;\n\n  potentialPayout: number;\n  userOdds: number;\n  refreshRound: () => void;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\n1. **Backend URL Pattern**: \n   - Single env var: `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` (points to backend root, e.g., `http://localhost:3100`)\n   - All routes use suffix: `/fairness/*` (coinflip, lord), `/closecall/*`, `/auth/*`\n   - Default fallback: `http://127.0.0.1:3100`\n\n2. **Polling & Event Detection**:\n   - Coinflip: WebSocket PDA monitoring + fallback polling (2-5s during active play)\n   - Close Call: Polling only (100ms for price, 5-30s for rounds)\n\n3. **Authorization**:\n   - Auth endpoints: No JWT required (`/auth/*`)\n   - Fairness endpoints: JWT Bearer token in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n\n4. **Price Feeds**:\n   - Pyth live WebSocket (configurable endpoint)\n   - Assets: BTC, ETH, SOL\n   - Direct consumption via `usePriceSubscription(asset)` hook\n\n5. **Data Flow**:\n   - Backend builds transactions, frontend signs and confirms on-chain\n   - Backend polls/watches on-chain events and settles via coordinator\n   - Frontend polls backend for settlement proof after on-chain event detected\n\nAll file paths are absolute and ready for reference."}],"totalDurationMs":179112,"totalTokens":77338,"totalToolUseCount":43,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1467,"cache_read_input_tokens":71065,"output_tokens":4806,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1467},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
